name: Nana Yōkai Collection: Nekomata
description:
Nana Yōkai Collection is a series of illustrations, created with the aim of sharing traditional Japanese mythology. In this series, Nana will be personifying herself as different Yōkai (Japanese spirits).
There are two different types, the beast that lives in the mountains and eats humans, and the ones raised domestically that grow old and transform. These last ones are said to have powers of necromancy, controlling death with ritualistic dances. The more badly treated a cat has been before its transformation, the more powerful it will become.
